<seg id="2703">This screen permits you to specify special actions to be taken whenever a text job is interrupted by another, higher priority, message. There are four kinds of speech jobs that & ktts; handles:</seg>
<seg id="2704">Screen Reader Output has the highest priority. It is reserved for use by Screen Reader applications. Screen Reader Output preempts all other messages, causing those jobs to pause. Once the Screen Reader Output has been spoken, the preempted jobs will automatically resume.</seg>
