<seg id="2959">The init binary is located in / sbin and not / etc. This is important as one might try and upgrade a machine to System V init without re-installing and reformatting. The & Linux; kernel looks in / etc for its init first, so you must make sure and delete your old init from there if any.</seg>
<seg id="2960">SysV init also differs from BSD init in that the config files are in a subfolder of / etc instead of residing directly in / etc. This folder is called rc. d. In there you will find rc. sysinit and the following folders:</seg>
