<seg id="2971">Here you learn how to use & ksysv;, which should n't be hard since it was designed to be as user-friendly as possible.</seg>
<seg id="2972">Using & ksysv; with a mouse or other pointing device is easy: just drag an entry from the Available Services area onto one of the six runlevels to start (or resp. stop) it in that runlevel.</seg>
<seg id="2973">You can also move scripts between runlevels, or change the position in a given runlevel, by dragging it around. Doing so removes the entry from its original runlevel (or position). This does n't happen when you drag an entry from the Available Services area.</seg>
